PLUG-IN-OUT ARCHITECTURE:
=========================
Static classes (like GroundPlaneGenerator) are utility modules that:
- Don't need to be attached to GameObjects
- Are called directly via static methods
- Are still part of the plug-in-out system as utility modules

Component classes (like MazeGenerator) are:
- Attached to GameObjects
- Can be configured via Inspector
- Can be enabled/disabled at runtime

Both types are valid plug-in modules, just used differently.

